  "playingCareerSummary": "Former India wicket-keeper batter: 5 Tests, 36 ODIs (1986-1992). Did not play in the IPL. The most successful domestic coach in Indian cricket history, with six Ranji Trophy titles (two with Mumbai, three with Vidarbha, one with Madhya Pradesh).",
  "bio": "KKR head coach from 2023 to 2025. Delivered KKR's third IPL title in 2024 with a dominant campaign — just 3 losses all season, 1st in the table, and the fastest run-chase in an IPL final. Worked alongside mentor Gautam Gambhir in 2024 (a partnership widely credited with the transformation). His disciplinarian reputation made him a contrast to the more player-led McCullum era. Stepped aside after his three-year contract ended in 2025.",
